+# 2D Call Graph Enhancements - Phase 2 Implementation Plan
+
+## Overview
+
+This document outlines the implementation plan to enhance the 2D call graph visualization with the following key requirements:
+
+1. **Node Titles**: Display symbol names directly on nodes in the graph view
+2. **Smooth Lines**: Implement smooth, continuous lines instead of dotted/scattered connections
+3. **Left-to-Right Flow**: Create a hierarchical layout that progresses from left to right
+
+## Current State Analysis
+
+### ✅ **What's Working:**
+- Basic 2D canvas rendering with nodes as rectangles
+- Edge connections as simple lines
+- Force-directed and Grid layout algorithms
+- Pan/zoom navigation
+- View switching between tree and 2D modes
+
+### 🔧 **Current Limitations:**
+1. **Text Rendering**: Node labels are commented out due to Canvas text complexity
+2. **Line Quality**: Using basic Line primitives which appear dotted in Braille mode
+3. **Layout Direction**: Force-directed layout has no directional bias, Grid layout doesn't respect call hierarchy
+
+## Implementation Plan
+
